\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Ajax, son of Telamon,\uc0\u8232 was the first to kill a man, brave Epicles,\u8232 companion of Sarpedon. Ajax hit him\u8232 with a massive jagged rock lying inside the wall,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[380]\u8232 near the top. No man now alive could heft that stone\u8232 in his two hands, not even someone young and strong,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0420\u8232 but Ajax raised it high, then hurled it, smashing\u8232 the man\'92s four-ridged helmet and completely crushing\u8232 his entire skull. Epicles fell, like a diver,\u8232 from that high tower, and his spirit left his bones.\u8232 Teucer struck mighty Glaucus, son of Hippolochus,\u8232 with an arrow shot from high up on the wall,\u8232 as Glaucus was moving up. He hit him on the arm,\u8232 on a part he saw exposed. That stopped Glaucus\'92 charge.\u8232 He climbed back down the wall, but stealthily,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[390]\u8232 so no Achaean man could see that he\'92d been hit\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0430\u8232 and boast aloud about it. Sarpedon was upset\u8232 at Glaucus\'92 departure, when he noticed it,\u8232 but he did not neglect to keep up the attack.\u8232 He lunged at Alcmaon, Thestor\'92s son, speared him well,\u8232 then yanked his spear back, which pulled Alcmaon with it.\u8232 He fell forward\'97his finely decorated armour,\u8232 all of bronze, echoed as he crashed onto the ground.\u8232 With his strong hands, Sarpedon grabbed the parapet and pulled.\u8232 The whole construction fell apart, breaching the wall,\u8232 creating a passage through for many men.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0440\
