\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0With these words, he drove them on.\uc0\u8232 Their ears all caught his call. Hurling themselves at the wall\u8232 in a dense mass, gripping sharp spears, they began to climb.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0490\u8232 Hector picked up a rock lying before the gates,\u8232 thick at its base but tapering sharply on the top.\u8232 Two of the best working men now living\u8232 could not lever that stone out of the ground easily\u8232 into their cart, but Hector carried it with ease alone.\u8232 Crooked-minded Cronos\'92 son made it light for him.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[450]\u8232 Just as a shepherd has no trouble carrying\u8232 a ram\'92s fleece in one hand, hardly noticing the weight,\u8232 so Hector lifted up that rock, then carried it\u8232 straight to the doors guarding the strongly fitted gates,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0500\u8232 high double doors with two cross pieces holding them inside\u8232 secured with a single bolt. Hector moved up closer,\u8232 planted himself before the doors, his legs wide apart\u8232 to throw with greater force, then hurled that rock\u8232 right at the centre of the doors. He smashed both hinges.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[460]\u8232 The stone\'92s momentum took it clear through the doors.\u8232 The gates groaned loudly. The bolts were sheared right off.\u8232 The impact of that boulder shattered all the planks.\u8232 Glorious Hector, his face like night\'92s swift darkness,\u8232 leapt inside. The bronze which covered his whole body\'